title: GJRMP_ACEC
name: GJRMP_ACEC
description:
Draft Resource Management Plan and Environmental Impact Statement, published December 2012

Theme: ACEC

Description: Final file of Areas of Critical Environmental Concern developed for the Resource Management Plan alternatives. These are the ACECs that were carried forward from the GJFO BLM's ACEC report, having been found to have the relevance and importance needed to be considered as an ACEC. Added Plateau Creek fall 2011. Removed Rapid Creek 2012 02 as per BLM Heidi Plank. 
Alternatives can be viewed by querying different alternatives' columns. A query of "Alt_AB= Yes" would display only those boundaries which are ACECs in alternative B. Conversely "Alt_B = No" would display those boundaries which are NOT ACECs considered in Alternative B.
Use the following query to determine alternative A
"Name" = 'Badger Wash 1987 RMP' OR 
"Name" = 'Palisade 1987 RMP' OR 
"Name" = 'Pyramid Rock 1987 RMP' OR 
"Name" = 'Rough Canyon 1987 RMP' OR 
"Name" = 'Unaweep Seep 1987 RMP'

Vintage: 2011.

Source: Data was derived from current ACEC GIS data, digitizing on 100k raster images, 2007 Mesa County Aerial Photography, Surface Land Ownership, staff and public input.

Capture Methodology: As stated above.

Steward: Collin Ewing, (970-244-3027).

Attribute: See Entity Attribute for further details.

Reliability: As per GJFO GIS data.

Intended use: Final data used in developing and displaying ACEC areas in RMP revision.

Quality Control: GJFO GIS staff.

Projection: UTM zone 13, Datum NAD 1983, Spheroid Clark 1866

Agency Contact: Doug Diekman, GIS Specialist 970-244-3087

NO WARRANTY IS MADE BY THE BUREAU OF LAND MANAGEMENT FOR THE USE
OF THE DATA FOR PURPOSES NOT INTENDED BY THE BUREAU.
